1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 44-04-19 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to the opportunity to provide public comment at a meeting of a public entity.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 44-04-19 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 44-04-19. Access to public meetings.
7 Except as otherwise specifically provided by law, all meetings of a public entity must be
8 open to the public. That portion of a meeting of the governing body of a public entity as defined
9 in subdivision c of subsection 13 of section 44-04-17.1 which does not regard public business is
10 not required to be open under this section.
11 1. This section is violated when any personan individual is denied access to a meeting
12 under this section, unless such refusal, implicitly or explicitly communicated, is due to
13 a lack of physical space in the meeting room for the personsindividual seeking access
14 or lack of electronic capacity to allow public viewing of the meeting through electronic
15 means.
16 2. For purposes of this section, if the meeting is held in person, the meeting room must
17 be accessible to, and the size of the room must accommodate, the number of
18 personsindividuals reasonably expected to attend the meeting. If the meeting is held
19 by electronic means, the electronic capacity must accommodate the number of
20 personsindividuals reasonably expected to attend the meeting remotely.
21 3. The right of a personan individual to attend a meeting under this section includes the
22 right to photograph, to record on audiotape or videotape, and to broadcast live on
23 radio or television the portion of the meeting that is not held in executive session,
24 provided there is no active interference with the conduct of the meeting. The exercise
