1 of this right may not be dependent upon the prior approval of the governing body.
2 However, the governing body may impose reasonable limitations on recording activity
3 to minimize the possibility of disruption of the meeting.
4 4. For meetings subject to this section, if the meeting is held through any electronic
5 means, the information necessary to join or view the meeting electronically must be
6 included in the notice issued under section 44-04-20.
7 5. A meeting of a public entity must include an opportunity for an individual in attendance
8 to provide public comment. A public comment:
9 a. May not be subject to approval by the public entity.
10 b. Only may be limited by time per speaker.
